resheaf is a presheaf supported at a single point: if `p₀ ∈ X` is a specified\npoint, then the skyscraper presheaf `𝓕` with value `A` is defined by `U ↦ A` if `p₀ ∈ U` and\n`U ↦ *` if `p₀ ∉ A` where `*` is some terminal object.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/Skyscraper.html#skyscraperPresheaf","kind":"def","line":51,"name":"skyscraperPresheaf","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Topology/Sheaves/Skyscraper.lean#L51-L68"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Topology.Sheaves.PUnit","Mathlib.Topology.Sheaves.Stalks","Mathlib.Topology.Sheaves.Functors"],"instances":[{"className":"CategoryTheory.Functor.IsRightAdjoint","name":"instIsRightAdjointPresheafSkyscraperPresheafFunctorOfHasColimits","typeNames":["skyscraperPresheafFunctor"]},{"className":"CategoryTheory.Functor.IsLeftAdjoint","name":"instIsLeftAdjointPresheafStalkFunctor","typeNames":["TopCat.Presheaf.stalkFunctor"]},{"className":"CategoryTheory.Functor.IsRightAdjoint","name":"instIsRightAdjointSheafSkyscraperSheafFunctorOfHasColimits","typeNames":["skyscraperSheafFunctor"]}],"name":"Mathlib.Topology.Sheaves.Skyscraper"}